{"nodes": [{"id": "projects_track_4_deepmind_b_proposal_claimthread", "label": "ClaimThread (FNOL Claims Agent with Persistent Claim File)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "projects/track-4-deepmind/b/proposal.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "projects_track_4_deepmind_b_proposal_teardown_proof", "label": "Teardown-and-Resume Proof (different rep, different machine)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "The process is killed on camera and a different rep on a different machine resumes the exact claim by environment ID \u2014 strictly harder than the brief's scheduled-resume example because the lookup key is a claimant/policy match spoken live that must resolve to the right env_id.", "source_file": "projects/track-4-deepmind/b/proposal.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "projects_track_4_deepmind_b_proposal_workforce_fungibility", "label": "Workforce Fungibility (any rep picks up mid-file)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "The provable claim isn't 'the same bot remembers' \u2014 it's that any employee can pick up mid-file, the actual staffing problem a CAT-surge carrier has (throw fresh headcount at a spike, not clone one bot).", "source_file": "projects/track-4-deepmind/b/proposal.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "projects_track_4_deepmind_b_proposal_deterministic_completeness_rule", "label": "Deterministic Completeness Rule (CHECK is code, not LLM)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Whether the claim file is enough to act on is decided by a rule over required fields and the document checklist, never an LLM guess \u2014 the only non-deterministic steps are translation quality and click-grounding, both behind a human-confirm gate.", "source_file": "projects/track-4-deepmind/b/proposal.md", "source_